      "writtenOn": "2026-06-19T21:08:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 3910: validate() now walks every reachable commit, tree, and blob header synchronously during loadConversations(). For long-lived conversations this can make daemon startup proportional to full repository history. Consider using libgit2\u0027s revwalk plus git_fsck-like object validation, caching a last-validated HEAD, or validating only after repository open failures/fetch-loop symptoms to avoid penalizing every clean startup.",
      "revId": "29bb42d7b5817df625a6c82dd4dbd7ea2dd79151",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
