      "writtenOn": "2026-06-19T21:08:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 3934: This only walks the tree for the first commit that owns a root-tree id. If a later commit reuses the same root tree but points to a parent whose commit object is missing, the commit lookup catches that; however, shared subtree ids are inserted by checkEntry before libgit2 descends into them. If the same subtree is referenced later after an earlier walk was interrupted by a missing object, it can be treated as already verified. Track verified objects only after successful traversal/read, or keep separate \u0027seen\u0027 and \u0027verified\u0027 sets so a failed traversal cannot mark entries valid.",
      "revId": "29bb42d7b5817df625a6c82dd4dbd7ea2dd79151",
